 <label>Setup Credentials</label>
    <row>
        <panel>
            <html>

              <h1>Encryption of Credentials</h1>
              <p>
                  If you require an encrypted credential in your configuration , then you can enter it here.<br/>
                  Ensure that the <code>username</code> you enter here matches the <code>jndi_user</code> or <code>destination_user</code> in your configuration<br/>
                  If you need to setup duplicate usernames , you can enter them with a <code>"//"</code> prefix notation , <code>foo//admin</code> , <code>goo//admin</code><br/>
              </p>
               <hr/>
                <h2>Enter Your Credentials To Encrypt</h2>
                
              <form>
                <div class="ck_div_input_fields">
                  <p class="helpText"><a href="#" class="add_credential_keys">Click to add more Credentials</a></p>

                         <!-- form fields -->

                   </div>

                   <div id="ck_form_buttons">

                      <button type="button" id="ck_cancel_button"> Cancel </button> 
                      <button type="button" id="ck_submit_button"> Save </button>

                   </div>

                </form>


            </html>
        </panel>
    </row>
</dashboard>